 Robert Bates , 73 , appeared in Tulsa district court on Tuesday and pleaded not guilty to second-degree manslaughter over the death of Eric Harris , who was killed during a botched sting on April 2 .
In the incident there have been allegations Bates was not properly trained and he told he could do whatever he wanted .
In 2009 , the Tulsa Sheriff 's Office concluded after an internal investigation that Bates had received special treatment during training and while working as a reserve deputy .